00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:54,780
Listen, I am sorry, but even over at the Törl, there's no trace of chamois.

575
00:31:54,850 --> 00:31:56,600
They must be have changed over to the Kar.

576
00:31:56,740 --> 00:31:59,860
Well, what did I tell you Petra? No game far and wide.

577
00:32:20,380 --> 00:32:21,180
There you go.

578
00:32:21,460 --> 00:32:22,520
Thanks.

579
00:32:22,820 --> 00:32:25,820
Well, what do your textbooks tell you about the wind?

580
00:32:26,710 --> 00:32:28,830
Well south wind. This means change of weather.

581
00:32:28,830 --> 00:32:30,060
Taking half hourly barometer readings...

582
00:32:30,060 --> 00:32:31,750
Well, do you by chance carry a barometer?

583
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:32,860
Naturally not.

584
00:32:32,860 --> 00:32:35,160
Well now that's stupid. Were do we take the readings?

585
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:36,780
Perhaps from the sky? Look up sometime.

586
00:32:39,030 --> 00:32:40,970
What do you think is going on

587
00:32:40,970 --> 00:32:42,260
Well, that means...

588
00:32:42,260 --> 00:32:44,680
That means, we have to return home quickly.

589
00:32:46,440 --> 00:32:49,090
Sooner or later, there will be a great snowstorm.

590
00:32:56,980 --> 00:32:57,770
What was that?

591
00:32:57,850 --> 00:33:00,370
As a hunter you should know how a gunshot sounds.

592
00:33:00,380 --> 00:33:01,870
Yes, but that could only be a poacher.

593
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:05,460
Yes, with all logical foresight, there's only this possibility.

594
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:08,290
Mathias, you're just hostile to him.

595
00:33:08,290 --> 00:33:10,430
I can't stand those vain theorists.

596
00:33:10,430 --> 00:33:11,620
But he isn't one.

597
00:33:11,860 --> 00:33:14,730
Oh, I see. You already concerned yourself with this Mister?

598
00:33:14,730 --> 00:33:15,910
And what if it would be so?

599
00:33:16,050 --> 00:33:17,530
I'm old enough actually.

600
00:33:17,530 --> 00:33:18,160
What for?

601
00:33:18,290 --> 00:33:20,160
To form my own opinion.

602
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,090
There's more about Bernd than you think.

603
00:33:22,090 --> 00:33:23,570
Well he has to show that first.

604
00:33:24,220 --> 00:33:24,980
Give me.

605
00:33:28,470 --> 00:33:29,940
Stop! Freeze!

606
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:44,730
I said, freeze!

607
00:33:45,570 --> 00:33:47,220
I am standing here the whole time.

608
00:33:47,220 --> 00:33:48,370
Where's your rifle?

609
00:33:48,790 --> 00:33:49,830
What rifle?

610
00:33:49,830 --> 00:33:51,750
Don't play-act. You shot just now.

611
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,420
Oh, somebody shot?

612
00:33:53,760 --> 00:33:55,390
Well, who could that be?

613
00:33:55,390 --> 00:33:56,680
You accurately will be told that.

614
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:57,950
You are under arrest.

615
00:33:58,320 --> 00:33:59,200
I!?

616
00:33:59,320 --> 00:34:00,480
Arrested?

617
00:34:00,850 --> 00:34:01,660
Well,

618
00:34:01,750 --> 00:34:03,360
can't do anything about it.

619
00:34:03,490 --> 00:34:05,130
Watch out, falling rocks!

620
00:34:14,190 --> 00:34:15,870
Come out. It's of no use.

621
00:34:27,390 --> 00:34:29,240
Well that's typical of that old crook.

622
00:34:29,240 --> 00:34:31,040
Yes and I am the disgraced.

623
00:34:31,180 --> 00:34:32,980
Don't worry, Bernd.

624
00:34:33,140 --> 00:34:35,680
No forester ever could stand up to Gustl Wegrainer.

625
00:34:35,710 --> 00:34:37,510
Ah, I was right then. He does poach.

626
00:34:37,510 --> 00:34:39,070
Since he's able to hold a rifle.

627
00:34:39,290 --> 00:34:41,350
You know that and don't do anything against it?

628
00:34:41,410 --> 00:34:43,940
Correct. But he's only shooting with blanks.

629
00:34:44,500 --> 00:34:45,550
Dirty trick.

630
00:34:45,670 --> 00:34:47,610
Well now that doesn't suit you, too.

631
00:34:47,860 --> 00:34:51,070
The Wegrainer Gustl is in principle a much better hunter than most.

632
00:34:51,230 --> 00:34:53,320
He doesn't have to shoot at all costs, like those, who don't care...

633
00:34:53,320 --> 00:34:55,650
and who shoot too, if the game is starved in the winter.

634
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:58,470
What's the real hunter's passion?

635
00:34:58,850 --> 00:35:00,160
It's the stalking.

636
00:35:00,380 --> 00:35:03,050
And if you get a good look on the buck you're after.

637
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:05,330
And you are sure to place a good shot.

638
00:35:05,330 --> 00:35:06,450
then you pull the trigger.

639
00:35:06,580 --> 00:35:07,820
What's happening then...

640
00:35:07,820 --> 00:35:09,080
has more in common with butchery...

641
00:35:09,080 --> 00:35:10,770
than with the art of hunting.

642
00:35:11,060 --> 00:35:14,120
Yes, Gustl always takes the best of the hunt.

643
00:35:14,370 --> 00:35:16,250
And he will be grateful for ever,

644
00:35:16,250 --> 00:35:19,510
that you just gave him the feeling today, to be a poacher.

645
00:35:19,580 --> 00:35:21,400
Are there still actual poachers?

646
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,330
Oh yes.

647
00:35:22,330 --> 00:35:23,450
I don't understand that.

648
00:35:23,450 --> 00:35:27,110
Today it's much easier to buy game in a venison store.

649
00:35:27,230 --> 00:35:29,060
Today's poachers are the lords of the hunting grounds,

650
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:32,940
who shoot the bucks who weren't approved by their own hunters.

651
00:35:36,980 --> 00:35:37,960
M hm,

652
00:35:38,250 --> 00:35:39,350
it's starting now.

653
00:35:39,460 --> 00:35:40,380
What?

654
00:35:40,380 --> 00:35:41,860
You cannot do that!

655
00:35:41,860 --> 00:35:43,450
Hello! Hello!

656
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:45,610
What's up?

657
00:35:45,610 --> 00:35:47,660
You cannot ride the material elevator.

658
00:35:47,660 --> 00:35:49,060
The storm is too strong.

659
00:35:49,060 --> 00:35:49,940
Not ride?

660
00:35:49,940 --> 00:35:51,190
That doesn't work, else broken.

661
00:35:51,190 --> 00:35:53,490
Better feel cold here, then break your neck.

662
00:35:53,670 --> 00:35:54,770
I have to get down.

663
00:35:54,770 --> 00:35:55,850
That's not going to work, Marcello.

664
00:35:55,850 --> 00:35:57,420
If not going, I go.

665
00:35:57,580 --> 00:35:58,670
Bella!

666
00:36:00,230 --> 00:36:02,630
Man, you're crazy. You can't see your hand in front of your face.

667
00:36:02,630 --> 00:36:04,500
I have to get down. Addio.

668
00:36:04,500 --> 00:36:06,560
Let go of your rendezvous then.

669
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:09,120
Bella.

670
00:36:12,930 --> 00:36:15,890
If you misstep in the wall, you'll fall to your death.

671
00:36:15,960 --> 00:36:16,740
Awful weather,

672
00:36:16,850 --> 00:36:18,190
it's snowing on the top.

673
00:36:18,340 --> 00:36:19,460
At this season.

674
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:21,670
This only happens once in a blue moon.

675
00:36:22,140 --> 00:36:23,290
Well look around.

676
00:36:24,270 --> 00:36:27,310
It's a crime how badly this bank is secured against burglary.

677
00:36:27,310 --> 00:36:28,210
Why?

678
00:36:28,730 --> 00:36:29,950
No bars.

679
00:36:30,690 --> 00:36:33,340
The safe is sardine can for nitro blowtorches.

680
00:36:33,410 --> 00:36:34,090
You think?

681
00:36:34,830 --> 00:36:36,370
One really ponders,

682
00:36:36,610 --> 00:36:37,960
to bring your money here.

683
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,310
Tell me about it.

684
00:36:42,110 --> 00:36:44,870
Good day, you still know me. Kubesch is my name. Ferdinand Kubesch.

685
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:46,610
I'd like some information.

686
00:36:46,610 --> 00:36:47,110
Sure.

687
00:36:47,110 --> 00:36:49,580
Concerning an account for me.

688
00:36:49,890 --> 00:36:50,970
A checking account.

689
00:36:51,390 --> 00:36:54,040
Well I don't know the nicknames of these things.

690
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:56,680
I think of an account, where I get more

691
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:58,270
money back then I

692
00:36:58,270 --> 00:36:58,990
payed in.

693
00:36:58,990 --> 00:37:00,060
A savings account.

694
00:37:00,180 --> 00:37:01,210
Yes, I think that's it.

695
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:08,120
Bella.

696
00:37:09,330 --> 00:37:10,380
For heavens sake.

697
00:37:11,550 --> 00:37:13,120
Marcello's rosary.

698
00:37:14,150 --> 00:37:15,740
Something must have happened.

699
00:37:18,860 --> 00:37:20,720
Mr. Burger, please cover for me at the counter.

700
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:21,480
Of course.

701
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:23,170
Come, well come,

702
00:37:28,950 --> 00:37:30,050
Mr. engineer.

703
00:37:30,050 --> 00:37:30,540
Yes.

704
00:37:30,540 --> 00:37:32,550
Something must have happened, to Marcello.

705
00:37:32,550 --> 00:37:33,760
Nothing happened.

706
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:36,250
He had to stay at mid-station with the other workers.

707
00:37:36,480 --> 00:37:39,510
We couldn't risk using the material elevator.

708
00:37:39,910 --> 00:37:41,220
But look at the dog.

709
00:37:41,220 --> 00:37:42,690
Something has happened.

710
00:37:43,310 --> 00:37:45,390
It brought this. Marcello's rosary.

711
00:37:45,560 --> 00:37:47,390
He wouldn't be that crazy...

712
00:37:47,670 --> 00:37:48,800
Calm yourself down.

713
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,070
We talk to the mid-station.

714
00:37:50,070 --> 00:37:51,450
He's there for sure.

715
00:38:21,730 --> 00:38:23,070
Hm, the line is torn.

716
00:38:31,620 --> 00:38:33,880
We call the mountain rescue service.

717
00:38:37,460 --> 00:38:39,340
Police Department Kaprun.

718
00:38:43,980 --> 00:38:46,080
Ok, I'll go fetch the people.

719
00:38:48,330 --> 00:38:49,710
Soo.

720
00:38:55,790 --> 00:38:56,450
Telephone.

721
00:38:56,450 --> 00:38:57,250
Well and?

722
00:38:57,310 --> 00:38:58,260
Well.

723
00:39:04,220 --> 00:39:04,970
Hello?

724
00:39:04,970 --> 00:39:06,520
Forest administration.

725
00:39:08,870 --> 00:39:10,750
Someone's stuck in the rock face.

726
00:39:10,950 --> 00:39:12,150
Just a moment.

727
00:39:12,990 --> 00:39:13,890
Gimme!

728
00:39:14,090 --> 00:39:14,970
Yes. ...

729
00:39:18,520 --> 00:39:20,090
the climbing iron rope.

730
00:39:20,090 --> 00:39:21,090


731
00:39:21,100 --> 00:39:21,950
My things too.

732
00:39:21,950 --> 00:39:23,470
We will fetch the dog shortly.

733
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:26,020
You stay here, it's difficult enough to get one person out of the wall.

734
00:39:26,120 --> 00:39:28,350
I bring to your attention, that I am obliged

735
00:39:28,350 --> 00:39:29,960
to participate in every rescue operation.

736
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:30,970
Well then...

737
00:39:39,890 --> 00:39:41,430
We notify you, as soon as we find him.

738
00:39:41,430 --> 00:39:42,380
Thanks, gentlemen.

739
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:43,510
Well then.

740
00:39:50,670 --> 00:39:53,020
Look, your rope unfastened. I tuck it in there.

741
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:54,510
They are coming already.

742
00:39:54,510 --> 00:39:55,420
Thank God!

743
00:39:55,420 --> 00:39:56,800
I can't stand this rain.

744
00:39:58,970 --> 00:39:59,780
Come!

745
00:39:59,830 --> 00:40:00,710
Awful weather.

746
00:40:00,710 --> 00:40:02,260
Let's march.

747
00:40:34,260 --> 00:40:35,240
No, thanks.

748
00:40:35,240 --> 00:40:36,050
Drink.

749
00:40:36,050 --> 00:40:38,400
You don't help anybody, if you torture yourself.

750
00:40:41,410 --> 00:40:42,490
Stupid of me.

751
00:40:43,230 --> 00:40:44,160
Strange.

752
00:40:46,190 --> 00:40:46,820
What?

753
00:40:46,820 --> 00:40:48,820
I planed to talk with you.

754
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:51,120
And now, we sit together and it doesn't work again.

755
00:40:52,460 --> 00:40:53,410
It doesn't work?

756
00:40:54,110 --> 00:40:54,880
Well,

757
00:40:55,970 --> 00:40:57,390
I can guess already.

758
00:40:57,400 --> 00:40:58,170
Let's leave it.

759
00:40:58,170 --> 00:40:59,880
It doesn't suit some people in the village.

760
00:40:59,980 --> 00:41:01,480
It's not meant this way.

761
00:41:01,950 --> 00:41:03,630
That's nobody's business.

762
00:41:03,910 --> 00:41:06,210
Is an italian a worse person?

763
00:41:06,310 --> 00:41:08,930
These things doesn't have anything to do with nationality.

764
00:41:09,070 --> 00:41:11,500
Then what you're saying is, that Marcello is bad person.

765
00:41:11,500 --> 00:41:12,460
Not that either.

766
00:41:12,620 --> 00:41:15,690
But I want to save you from disappointment.

767
00:41:16,050 --> 00:41:19,780
Love is something different than living your life together.

768
00:41:20,220 --> 00:41:22,200
Only if you are very lucky,

769
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:24,390
both things come together.

770
00:41:24,830 --> 00:41:26,620
I know, in the beginning you always think,

771
00:41:26,620 --> 00:41:29,020
you belong together because you love.

772
00:41:29,260 --> 00:41:32,250
You only think that because you want it to be.

773
00:41:32,540 --> 00:41:35,040
But why shouldn't we belong together?

774
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:37,230
I never knew,

775
00:41:37,420 --> 00:41:39,260
a man could be this tender.

776
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:41,780
This touching and funny.

777
00:41:42,960 --> 00:41:44,060
Do you understand that?

778
00:41:44,140 --> 00:41:47,390
I do, but in every person there are different things, too.

779
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:50,140
Marcello for example is hot-tempered beyond measure.

780
00:41:50,330 --> 00:41:53,080
I met him as he nearly killed a person.

781
00:41:53,150 --> 00:41:55,020
It's no use to talk him down.

782
00:41:55,020 --> 00:41:56,220
I don't want to.

783
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:58,030
I just wanted to make clear,

784
00:41:58,030 --> 00:42:00,450
that fitting together is not as easy

785
00:42:00,460 --> 00:42:02,020
as one would like it to be.

786
00:42:02,980 --> 00:42:04,500
You should have seen that.

787
00:42:04,620 --> 00:42:07,460
She became completely pale as the dog came in through the door.

788
00:42:07,590 --> 00:42:08,520
White as the wall.

789
00:42:08,520 --> 00:42:11,020
And why? Because the fears for her dirty Macaroni.

790
00:42:11,890 --> 00:42:13,270
That's a disgrace.

791
00:42:13,440 --> 00:42:15,840
These, these foreigners take away our poshest girls.

792
00:42:15,980 --> 00:42:17,070
Do we need that?

793
00:42:17,260 --> 00:42:18,660
Yes, hear, hear!

794
00:42:18,810 --> 00:42:21,310
Well, if she was yours. Please, whatever.

795
00:42:21,470 --> 00:42:23,710
But Ms. Raiffeisen bank executive,

796
00:42:23,900 --> 00:42:25,130
that's entirely different.

797
00:42:25,470 --> 00:42:26,670
Schnucki, another one.

798
00:42:26,670 --> 00:42:28,330
Another one? That's already the forth.

799
00:42:28,330 --> 00:42:30,180
So what? I do pay.

800
00:42:30,180 --> 00:42:31,860
It's just because of the driving.

801
00:42:32,900 --> 00:42:34,830
After the 8th double, I drive best.

802
00:42:35,810 --> 00:42:37,520
You really have to think about

803
00:42:37,700 --> 00:42:40,200
depositing your money in this bank.

804
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:41,890
You don't have anything to pay in.

805
00:42:42,570 --> 00:42:43,240
Good one.

806
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:45,100
That's not funny,

807
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:46,790
suddenly you money is gone.

808
00:42:46,790 --> 00:42:48,130
Don't talk nonsense.

809
00:42:48,130 --> 00:42:50,710
Ms. Hirt embezzling. That's outrageous.

810
00:42:50,710 --> 00:42:52,200
Not her. But the foreign workers.

811
00:42:52,200 --> 00:42:54,090
There are enough crooks among them.

812
00:42:55,360 --> 00:42:56,950
I wouldn't be surprised,

813
00:42:56,950 --> 00:42:59,010
if he just came on to her,

814
00:42:59,260 --> 00:43:01,320
to access the bank more easily.

815
00:43:02,740 --> 00:43:03,690
In the night.

816
00:43:46,080 --> 00:43:47,500
Here I am,

817
00:43:48,380 --> 00:43:50,020
here!

818
00:44:01,120 --> 00:44:02,490
He's hanging below there.

819
00:44:03,180 --> 00:44:04,450
You can't do anything now.

820
00:44:04,530 --> 00:44:05,800
The wind will blow you out of the wall.

821
00:44:05,870 --> 00:44:07,400
We have to wait until the storm calms down.

822
00:44:07,400 --> 00:44:08,670
Hopefully, he can hold on that long.

823
00:44:08,670 --> 00:44:10,090
Help!

824
00:44:10,460 --> 00:44:11,290
I go get him.

825
00:44:11,290 --> 00:44:12,590
Don't try a bravura performance.

826
00:44:13,280 --> 00:44:14,280
Let's go.

827
00:44:22,580 --> 00:44:24,110
I can't bear it.

828
00:44:24,250 --> 00:44:25,900
We cannot do anything at all.

829
00:44:27,210 --> 00:44:28,780
I go meet him.

830
00:44:30,260 --> 00:44:31,600
Just part of the way.

831
00:44:31,600 --> 00:44:32,710
I'll come along.

832
00:46:10,730 --> 00:46:11,890
Marcello!

833
00:46:18,550 --> 00:46:19,680
Marcello.

834
00:46:20,290 --> 00:46:21,860
I didn't happen much.

835
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:23,090
He sprained his ankle

836
00:46:23,190 --> 00:46:24,950
and he's a bit frozen.

837
00:46:25,150 --> 00:46:26,620
Bring him in to me.

838
00:46:26,860 --> 00:46:28,130
I call the doctor.

839
00:46:28,470 --> 00:46:30,270
Yes, then everything's fine.

840
00:46:41,780 --> 00:46:42,900
Good bye.

841
00:46:46,980 --> 00:46:49,160
Marcello, don't talk.

842
00:47:41,760 --> 00:47:43,310
He takes her home every night.

843
00:47:43,310 --> 00:47:44,780
But he only leaves in the morning.

844
00:47:44,780 --> 00:47:46,900
Gossip, nothing else but gossip

845
00:47:47,660 --> 00:47:49,210
Well, ask Kubesch.

846
00:47:49,360 --> 00:47:50,850
He saw it with his own eyes.

847
00:47:50,850 --> 00:47:51,730
Alright, Mr. Kubesch?

848
00:47:51,730 --> 00:47:52,390
What's up?

849
00:47:52,390 --> 00:47:54,130
Ms. executive with the Macaroni.

850
00:47:54,130 --> 00:47:56,240
